Open up a new finder window. Click Go->Go To Folder...
Type "/etc/resolv.conf" and then press Go.
A file will be selected, right click on it and press Get Info.
In the window you can now see "Original: /private/var/run/resolv.conf".
You can now click Go->Go To Folder... and type the path you just found and press enter.
A file will be selected and if you right click on it and choose More Info,
you will see the path under "General:" after "Where:".
So the complete path is /private/var/run/resolv.conf
